        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(queue): persist followup queues across gateway restarts",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nWhen the gateway process restarts, followup messages queued during an active agent turn are silently lost.\n\n## Solution\n\nPersist followup queues in shared SQLite (`followup_queue_entries`), migrate legacy JSON sidecars via doctor, rehydrate from live config, and wake restored routes on gateway startup so production idle-kick can drain them.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Followup messages queued during an active Telegram turn survive gateway restart and can be delivered afterward without silent loss.\n- Real environment tested: Local machine `joseph-MS-7B51`, systemd `openclaw-gateway.service`, Telegram DM chatId `6300969793`, sessionKey `agent:main:telegram:slash:6300969793`, build `920cc1153`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n  1. `pnpm build` in `~/dev/openclaw`; fix `models.providers.codex.api` → `openai-chatgpt-responses`; `systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway`.\n  2. Stop gateway; seed `followup_queue_entries` with marker `LIVE_PROOF_TG_1780458928` (864-byte row includes `sessionId`); `systemctl --user start openclaw-gateway`.\n  3. `openclaw agent --session-key agent:main:telegram:slash:6300969793 --to 6300969793 --channel telegram --deliver --message \"<read oldest pending followup>\"`.\n  4. `pnpm exec vitest run` on persist/drain-restart/gateway-recovery/roundtrip shards (head `920cc1153`).\n- Evidence after fix (redacted runtime log / copied live output):\n  - Journal: `[followup-queue-recovery] requested heartbeat wake for 1 restored followup queue route(s)`\n  - Journal: `[telegram] outbound send ok accountId=default chatId=6300969793 messageId=4122` and `4123`\n  - Agent JSON payload text: `Telegram live restart proof: reply with exactly LIVE_PROOF_TG_1780458928`, `deliverySucceeded: true`\n  - SQLite row length 864 unchanged immediately after restart (sessionId `7bb5f88d-6d65-4497-a6f3-bda08aafd33f`)\n  - Artifacts: `~/.openclaw/workspace/logs/followup-live-proof-final-20260603T035500Z/`\n- Observed result after fix: Restored followup prompt text was read from persisted queue and delivered to Telegram after gateway restart; transport and gateway healthy after rebuild.\n- What was not tested: Full mid-turn Telegram ingress enqueue (message #2 while turn #1 running) in this harness; Mantis capture.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: Proof used controlled SQLite seed plus agent turn to read/deliver restored prompt; production mid-turn enqueue path additionally covered by Vitest `drains restored items via production enqueue idle-kick after restart`.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/queue/persist.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/queue.drain-restart.test.ts src/gateway/server-followup-queue-recovery.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/queue.followup-restart-roundtrip.test.ts` — 39 passed locally on head `920cc1153`\n- CI green on prior pushes to this branch",
